A highly detailed, technical blueprint-style developer infographic poster on the theme of "WHEN FLOW BECOMES UNMAINTAINABLE".
Overall Theme: High-tech dark mode developer dashboard, cybersecurity blueprint, with sharp glowing lines and neat borders.
Colors: Deep dark navy background with glowing neon blue, electric cyan, warning red, and success green highlights.

Header:
- A prominent top-center glowing blue header: "WHEN FLOW BECOMES UNMAINTAINABLE".
- Below it, a clean subtitle: "The Warning Signs and the Apex Refactor Pattern" with a small Salesforce logo on the top-left and an "APEX BEST PRACTICES" badge on the top-right.

Section 1: "WHY IT MATTERS" (Top Row, 3 Horizontal Cards)
- "Admins Own Flow" with a person icon, "Devs Own Logic" with a layers icon, "Agentforce Calls Both" with a bot icon

Section 2: "THE COST" (Middle Row, Side-by-Side Comparison)
- Left Box (Red Theme): "FLOW ANTI-PATTERN — Logic That Must Move to Apex". Shows a red status pill "DANGER — ANTI-PATTERN".
- Right Box (Green Theme): "APEX PATTERN — Invocable Service Called by Flow". Shows a green status pill "SUCCESS — BEST PRACTICE".

Section 3: "CODE PATTERNS" (Main Center)
- Left Column (Bad Code in Red Border):
  - Heading: "// BAD"
  - Code block:
    // Record-triggered Flow doing what Apex should own:
// Get Records element INSIDE loop (SOQL in loop)
// 300+ nodes, no version history legible
// SLA recalc logic duplicated across 3 flows
// Fails silently at 200 records (CPU timeout)
// No unit tests possible for the SLA algorithm
- Right Column (Good Code in Green Border):
  - Heading: "// GOOD"
  - Code block:
    @InvocableMethod(label='Recalculate SLA Tier')
public static List<SlaResult> recalculate(
  List<SlaRequest> reqs
) {
  // Flow: detects CaseStatusChange event
  // Apex: owns SLA algorithm, fully tested
  // Reused by: Flow + LWC + Queueable + Agentforce
}

Section 4: "DEVELOPER PROFILE & CHECKLIST" (Bottom Row)
- Left Side: A 3D Pixar-style cartoon avatar portrait of a dark-skinned South Asian male with a full thick black beard, shoulder-length wavy dark hair pulled up into a messy top bun, warm friendly smile showing teeth, wearing a grey crew-neck sweatshirt with the word "MAGNETIC" on it, set against a warm orange bokeh background. The avatar is labeled "Bennie Joseph | Salesforce Architect". Next to it is a quote bubble: "Architecting intuitive systems, engineering scalable solutions."
- Right Side: A checklist with points: "Flow is for process orchestration — not for algorithms", "Move any loop-with-SOQL from Flow to Apex immediately", "Invocable Apex is reusable: Flow + LWC + Agentforce 2.0", "Write Apex unit tests for every business rule that matters", "Flow detects events — Apex implements the actual logic".
- Footer: A thin bar with icons for "Flow Builder", "Apex v64.0", "@InvocableMethod", "Agentforce 2.0" and the text "CODE SMART. AUTOMATE FASTER. DELIVER EXCELLENCE."

Style Details: Super high resolution, technical drawing grid, razor-sharp white and neon text, crisp layout, developer IDE aesthetic, flat vector graphics with subtle glow, highly legible monospace font for code blocks, professional presentation.

A highly detailed, technical blueprint-style developer infographic poster on the theme of "HYBRID PATTERN: FLOW + APEX".
Overall Theme: High-tech dark mode developer dashboard, cybersecurity blueprint, with sharp glowing lines and neat borders.
Colors: Deep dark navy background with glowing neon blue, electric cyan, warning red, and success green highlights.

Header:
- A prominent top-center glowing blue header: "HYBRID PATTERN: FLOW + APEX".
- Below it, a clean subtitle: "The Production Architecture That Lets Admins and Devs Work Together" with a small Salesforce logo on the top-left and an "APEX BEST PRACTICES" badge on the top-right.

Section 1: "WHY IT MATTERS" (Top Row, 3 Horizontal Cards)
- "Admin Visibility" with a person icon, "Eng Testability" with a shield icon, "Agent Ready" with a bot icon

Section 2: "THE COST" (Middle Row, Side-by-Side Comparison)
- Left Box (Red Theme): "ALL IN FLOW — Fragile, Untestable at Scale". Shows a red status pill "DANGER — ANTI-PATTERN".
- Right Box (Green Theme): "HYBRID — Flow Orchestrates, Apex Executes". Shows a green status pill "SUCCESS — BEST PRACTICE".

Section 3: "CODE PATTERNS" (Main Center)
- Left Column (Bad Code in Red Border):
  - Heading: "// BAD"
  - Code block:
    // All logic in Flow — the 300-node maze
// Get Records inside conditional path
// Duplicated assignment rules across flows
// Regression? Good luck reading the canvas.
// CPU timeout at 200 records → users see errors
// Agentforce cannot call complex flows reliably
- Right Column (Good Code in Green Border):
  - Heading: "// GOOD"
  - Code block:
    // Flow: lightweight orchestration only
When CaseStatusChanged {
  if (needsEscalation) {
    call RecalculateSlaAction  // typed Apex
    call SendEscalationEmail   // typed Apex
  }
}
// Apex: tested, bulkified, reusable by 4 callers

Section 4: "DEVELOPER PROFILE & CHECKLIST" (Bottom Row)
- Left Side: A 3D Pixar-style cartoon avatar portrait of a dark-skinned South Asian male with a full thick black beard, shoulder-length wavy dark hair pulled up into a messy top bun, warm friendly smile showing teeth, wearing a grey crew-neck sweatshirt with the word "MAGNETIC" on it, set against a warm orange bokeh background. The avatar is labeled "Bennie Joseph | Salesforce Architect". Next to it is a quote bubble: "Architecting intuitive systems, engineering scalable solutions."
- Right Side: A checklist with points: "Flow owns: process visibility, approval routing, simple assignments", "Apex owns: SLA rules, bulk DML, compliance logic, AI actions", "@InvocableMethod bridges both — same code from 4 entry points", "Agentforce 2.0 can call the same invocable actions as Flow", "Test Apex in isolation — do not rely on Flow to test Apex".
- Footer: A thin bar with icons for "Flow Orchestration", "Apex Services", "Invocable Actions", "Agentforce 2.0" and the text "CODE SMART. AUTOMATE FASTER. DELIVER EXCELLENCE."

Style Details: Super high resolution, technical drawing grid, razor-sharp white and neon text, crisp layout, developer IDE aesthetic, flat vector graphics with subtle glow, highly legible monospace font for code blocks, professional presentation.
